Package: PISAoccupations
Title: Explore relationship between students' perfomance and parents' occupations in PISA studies.
Version: 1.1.0 
Authors@R: c(
  person("PrzemysÅ‚aw", "Biecek", role = "aut",
    email = "przemyslaw.biecek@gmail.com"),
  person("Mateusz", "Staniak", role = "cre",
    email = "mateusz.staniak@math.uni.wroc.pl")
  )
Description: This package helps explore relationship between students' performance and parents' occupations 
    by providing tools for importing data from .txt files which can be found on OECD website, calculating 
    students' average performance with standard error grouped by chosen variables, exporting the results and creating basic plots.
    Data with calculated averages grouped just by parents' occupations and students' sex is included in the package.
    Shiny application presenting that data from different perspectives is also included.
